    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with a high-ceiling core, anchored by **Jackson Merrill** (74.85) and **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (74.84). **Jackson Merrill** is our primary target against Taillon; he benefits from a massive 23% boost driven by his leadoff spot and a favorable platoon matchup. Meanwhile, **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** serves as our offensive anchor, capitalizing on a weak 4.55 xERA opponent and a significant BvP edge. **Kyle Tucker** (73.39) and **Josh Lowe** (71.68) round out a formidable outfield, with **Josh Lowe** specifically positioned to exploit the high xERA of Fedde. Crucially, **Josh Lowe** receives a sneaky boost from his stolen base potential against a slow-working pitcher, aligning with our priority of targeting elite speed.\n\nOur most difficult roster decision involved **Brady House**, who sat on the bubble with a 43.97 score but was ultimately squeezed out by the efficiency of our middle-of-the-pack starters. While **Brady House** has utility, the optimizer preferred the stability of **Miguel Vargas** and the positional versatility offered by our current UTIL slot, **Marcell Ozuna**. Caution is advised regarding **Heliot Ramos** (46.99); while his score remains in the marginal tier, the 40% rain risk creates a volatility floor that could necessitate a pivot if a late-afternoon postponement occurs. Furthermore, we are actively monitoring the \"Lineup Pending\" tags for **Drake Baldwin**, **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.**, **Nasim Nunez**, **Jacob Wilson**, and **Marcell Ozuna**. Should any of these players drop in the order or be rested, their efficiency scores will crater, and we will be forced to look toward the bench, where **Josh Jung** remains ready as a fallback despite his own challenging matchup against a tough arm.",
